<br>
First I was the Support team, I ran the group of high levels to clear all the Giants until we got to the lair pulls. We had a warrior, a Paladin, a rogue (me), a cleric and a mage. We cleared 2 spiders, 2 icy terrors and 15 ice giants (not counting the 30 minute spawns maybe add another 8 there)<br>
<br>
Then we had to pull the Lair. Us high levels can’t pull because everytime Lady Vox’s sees us she Banishes us (Sends out to the zone into Permforst in Everfrost) and we have to run back in. We first tried our Enchanter we had (level 45) with some bad luck she fall into a pit. That was bad she was the only enchanter at the time and yes it took me almost an hour to get her out. Sorry next time you can try it with out an enchanter. When we did get her out I had a Cleric, mage and me as the support time. The Paladin had to leave and the Warrior changed to his Druid who was a healer in one of the groups. <br>
<br>
So then I Asked Azure to bring you all into the main room because I needed you to help kill the giants. It was never planned for you to fight them it was planned to have them cleared by the time you got there. Sorry we goofed. Ephron was assigned to me to help pull the lair spawns. Man the times that boy died for you guys isn’t funny, the amount of times the poor mage died who was in the support time was pretty sad to. &lt;Smile&gt; (Oh that was the pet you saw. The support team was in the room with you) After a number of tries (and Deaths) Ephron was able to pull half the stuff in the lair. That is what Cleric called /ooc giants inc I would have done it but I got Banished. I don’t care what you think. We all every single person did great. Not one death (well besides Ephron and the mage.) I’m sorry I didn’t get time to explain how to fight giants. It wasn’t the buff that made you land your spells it was range. You need to be in Melee Range to have spells land with Giants. The same reason you need to stand under Vox to hit her. It’s a high level monster thing. After that Ephron want in again and pulled the remaining Giants and Icy Terrors (Again great job bro) that had cleared the lair. The people that where in the support staff where in as much danger as you and had as much to loss or gain as everyone there. Everyone got rezed quickly by the Cleric, all the corpses got pulled from the Pits by me. In fact the support team had to clear the giants 2 times. All of them. We had an necromancer come and join us later and to buff you for the raid. And he also would have helped get the corpses out of the lair if you all had failed. You don’t know how luck you are to have a high level Cleric, necro and rogue there to help. You talk about staying alive as long as you did because of the buffs? You had level 57 and level 54 cleric buff on you. Giving you a lot of hit points and Armor class. Again for the support team and those Buffs don’t come for free. <br>
<br>
It takes everyone to win against Vox, when she died it was very very close there was only 2 tanks standing. Every nuke, every heal, bash stun, resist song, etc.. played a part in her dying. Those are things that support staff can’t do and I wish I could help in more then I do. Maybe that one backstab could be a matter of lossing or winning the fight?  <br>
<br>
As for loot and Exp. I’m sorry to report that’s not why people join the Dragon raids. It’s to do something you can’t do on your own. To be part of something bigger and larger then yourself. To do something that only a small number can and will do. You get the chance to kick a big bad dragon in the tail pipe and dance over her corpse. You go for the Kill, loot and exp is but a bonus. <br>
<br>
There is more to the Support team then just killing some giants and then rolling on loot. It’s filled with stress and knowing 50+ people’s lives or corpses are in your hands. And that Stress is only a small Fraction of what the Raid leader feels. And trust me I know.<br>
